{{Infobox person | name = Filopimin Finos | image = Filopimin Finos.jpg | birth_date = 1908 | birth_place = Modern [[Lokrida]] | death_date = {{Death date and age|1977|1|26|1908|1|1}} | death_place = [[Athens]] | othername = | occupation = [[Film Director]], [[actor]] | years_active = 1939–1977 | spouse = Linda Finou (1939–1977) | website = }}
'''Filopimin Finos''' ({{lang-el|Φιλοποίμην Φίνος}}; 1908 – January 26, 1977) was a [[Greece|Greek]] [[film producer]] of 186 films and the founder of [[Finos Film]], whose first film was in 1939. He built the first [[sound recording]] device in Greece, and shot the first [[colour film]] with [[stereo sound]]. Finos died in January 1977 after suffering cancer for seven years and he left no heir.
