'''Paul Caddick''' (born July 1950)<ref name="companieshouse1">{{cite web|url=https://beta.companieshouse.gov.uk/officers/yYpVo-Ec5TzdaJ0YENyJmM7hDqo/appointments |title=Paul CADDICK - Personal Appointments (free information from Companies House) |website=Beta.companieshouse.gov.uk |date= |accessdate=2017-01-18}}</ref> is a British businessman, founder of [[Caddick Group]], a civil engineering business, and [[Moda Living]], a property development company,<ref name="therichest1">{{cite web|url=http://www.therichest.com/celebnetworth/celebrity-business/property/paul-caddick-net-worth/ |title=Paul Caddick Net Worth |website=TheRichest.com |date= |accessdate=2017-01-18}}</ref> and is the director of 119 companies.<ref name="companieshouse1"/>
==Early life== Paul Caddick is the son of a miner.<ref name="insidermedia1">{{cite web|author= |url=https://www.insidermedia.com/yorkshire/entrepreneur/paul-caddick |title=Entrepreneur &#124; Insider Media Ltd |website=Insidermedia.com |date=2015-08-27 |accessdate=2017-01-18}}</ref>
==Career== Cadddick worked for [[West Yorkshire County Council]], [[John Laing plc|John Laing]] and the civil engineers [[Sir Lindsay Parkinson]], before starting his own business in 1980.<ref name="insidermedia1"/>
In 1997, he and [[Gary Hetherington]] bought [[Leeds Rhinos]] rugby league team, and they co-founded [[Leeds Rugby Limited]].<ref name="therichest1"/>
His net worth is estimated at £200 million.<ref>{{cite web | title=YEN Top 10 - Yorkshire Rich List | website=Yorkshire Enterprise Network | date=March 2, 2016 | url=https://www.yorkshirenetwork.co.uk/top-10/top-10-yorkshire-rich-list/ | access-date=April 1, 2018}}</ref>
