{{EngvarB|date=December 2017}} {{Use dmy dates|date=December 2017}} {{Infobox person | honorific_prefix = | name = Ragib Ali | honorific_suffix = | image = | image_size = 220px | alt = | caption = | native_name = রাগীব আলী | native_name_lang = bn | birth_name = | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|df=y|1936|10|10}} | birth_place = [[Bishwanath Upazila|Kamal bazar]], [[Sylhet District]] | death_date = | death_place = | death_cause = | resting_place = | residence = | nationality = Bangladeshi | other_names = | ethnicity = | citizenship = British, Bangladeshi | education = | alma_mater = Raza G.C High School of Sylhet | occupation = Entrepreneur, industrialist, tea-planter, [[educationalist]], banker | years_active = 1961–present | known_for = | notable_works = | home_town = | salary = | net_worth = {{increase}} $250&nbsp;million<ref name="worldsrichpeople">{{cite web |last=Loke|first=Steven|url=http://www.worldsrichpeople.com/richest-man-in-bangladesh.html|title=Richest Man in Bangladesh|publisher=The Richest People in the World|accessdate=1 December 2014}}</ref>/[[Bangladeshi taka|BDT]] 3.3&nbsp;billion | title = | term = | predecessor = | successor = | party = | boards = | spouse = Rabeya Khatun Chowdhury (died 12 December 2006) | partner = | children = 2 | parents = | relatives = | awards = | website = }}
'''Ragib Ali''' ({{lang-bn|রাগীব আলী}}; born 10 October 1938) is a Bangladeshi-born British industrialist,<ref name="thedailystar">{{cite news |url=http://www.thedailystar.net/story.php?nid=73717|title=Industrialist Ragib Ali sued|location=Bangladesh|work=[[The Daily Star (Bangladesh)|The Daily Star]]|date=31 January 2009|accessdate=24 April 2011}}</ref> pioneer tea-planter and [[educationalist]]. He is also associated with bank, insurance companies, and many other business houses. He is the founder of leading university, Sylhet In 2017, he was sentenced to 14 years in prison for corruption.
==Early life== Ali was born in Talibpur, [[Bishwanath Upazila|Bishwanath]], [[Sylhet District]], [[Bengal Presidency]] (now [[Bangladesh]]), [[British India]]. He has eight brothers.
Ali was educated in Bangladesh. He studied at the Raza G.C High School and College of Sylhet. In 1956, at the age of 18, he moved to the United Kingdom to further his education.
==Career== In 1961, after completing his education Ali started being involved in business. Once in the UK, he transformed himself from an ordinary waiter to a leading entrepreneur. He still has links with UK through his family members, who live in London as well as in [[Bradford]], the majority of his father's family now live in [[Croydon]], [[South London]].<ref name="bbwhoswho08">{{cite book |last1=Karim|first1=Mohammed Abdul|last2=Karim|first2=Shahadoth|title=British Bangladeshi Who's Who|url=http://www.bbwhoswho.co.uk/Profile/Ali,%20Mr%20Ragib.pdf|date=July 2008|publisher=British Bangla Media Group|page=44|isbn= |accessdate=1 May 2012}}</ref>
Ali is the Chairman of Sylhet Tea Company Ltd. and several other tea estates in [[Sylhet Division|Sylhet]] and [[Chittagong]]. He is also the managing director of Kohinoor Industries Ltd. He is the Chairman of [[Southeast Bank Limited]]. He has played a pioneering role in the tea industry. He is involved in charitable activities and has set up numerous trusts and educational institutions.<ref name="bbwhoswho08"/>
Ali is the founder chairman of [[Jalalabad Ragib-Rabeya Medical College]]. He is also the immediate past Chairman of [[North South University]] Foundation. He is also the founder of [[Leading University]] and [[University of Asia Pacific (Bangladesh)|University of Asia Pacific]]. He also contributed in many schools and established many colleges around Bangladesh.<ref name="bbwhoswho08"/>
== Controversy == The [[Bangladesh Anti Corruption Commission|Bangladeshi Anti-Corruption Commission]] (ACC) filed a case against him for amassing illegal wealth and concealing information about his assets.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/news-detail-73717|title=Industrialist Ragib Ali sued|author=|date=31 January 2009|website=thedailystar.net|accessdate=25 February 2018}}</ref> He was also accused of illegal occupation of property of the minority Hindu community which he was subsequently forced to give back.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://opinion.bdnews24.com/2016/05/23/our-hindu-problem/|title=Our Hindu problem|date=23 May 2016|website=The Opinion Pages|access-date=9 April 2017}}</ref> He along with his family fled to India to avoid arrest. However, they were sent back to Bangladesh after being arrested in Assam after their visa expired. He along with his son, Syed Abdul Hye, was convicted in court and Ragib was sentenced to 14 years in Jail on 6 April 2017. He had grabbed the land (tea estate) in 1990 after forcing the Shebayet (caretaker) Pankaj Kumar Gupta to flee to India.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.thedailystar.net/country/land-grabbing-sylhet-industrialist-ragib-ali-gets-14yrs-jail-1387306|title=Land grabbing: Sylhet industrialist Ragib Ali gets 14yrs’ jail|date=6 April 2017|work=The Daily Star|access-date=9 April 2017}}</ref> His daughter, son-in-law, and another relative were also convicted by the court.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://en.prothom-alo.com/bangladesh/news/144509/Ragib-Ali-gets-14-yrs-jail-in-land-grabbing-case|title=Ragib Ali gets 14 yrs jail in land grabbing case|work=Prothom Alo|access-date=9 April 2017}}</ref> However, he got bail on these cases on 29 October 2018 eleven months after the conviction from the Supreme Court.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.dhakatribune.com/bangladesh/nation/2017/10/30/ragib-son-released-jail/|title=Industrialist Ragib Ali, son released from Sylhet jail|date=2017-10-29|work=Dhaka Tribune|access-date=2018-05-13|language=en-US}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://bdnews24.com/bangladesh/2016/08/13/sylhet-industrialist-ragib-ali-family-flee-to-india-to-evade-arrest-over-hindu-land-grabbing|title=Sylhet industrialist Ragib Ali, family flee to India to evade arrest over Hindu land grabbing | date=13 August 2016 |work=bdnews24.com|access-date=5 November 2018}}</ref>
He has allegations of acts against Bangladesh during the liberation war in 1971 while staying abroad.{{fact|date=November 2018}} He is also allegations of occupying government properties.{{fact|date=November 2018}}
